The paper deals with automatic search of neural architectures for vision tasks, specifically dense per-pixel classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The methodology proposed in the paper involves the use of a recurrent neural network trained using reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with natural language tasks, albeit in a limited capacity, as it mentions the use of the methodology for natural language tasks as well. This could potentially place the paper under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper does not deal with any specific hardware or implementation details, ruling out the category of computer architecture (cs.AR).
